GL.iNet SDK4.0 API Online Docs
1、SDK 4.0 API Guide
API Description
The firmware API reference LuCI using JSON-RPC.
The http request path for all APIs is /rpc.
For example, if your device's LAN IP is 192.168.8.1, all request is
Plain Text
Copy
POST /rpc HTTP/1.1 Host: 192.168.8.1 Content-Type: application/json ...
Example of HTTP request
​
All APIs use call as the JSON-RPC method and the specific functions are written in JSON-RPC params, except for login/logout related APIs.
For APIs that require authentication, put the sid (authentication token) in the JSON-RPC params instead and NOT in the HTTP Header
JSON
Copy
{ "jsonrpc": "2.0", "method": "call", "params": [ "AlVv2SolJU3jezHDpreZ5KDm8102f09q", // sid "system", // module-name "get_status" // function_name ], "id": 0 }
Example of Json sent when the system/get_status API is called
​
The APIs does not yet support the JOSN-RPC standard feature of multiple functions in one request
Login and Use Steps
Step1: Get encryption parameters by challenge method
Call the challenge method and passing in the username to login as the username parameter. The username is fixed as root in standard firmware.
This method respond data for encryption, including:
alg
The enumeration value identifying the algorithm used for encryption.
1 → MD5
5 → SHA256
6 → SHA512
salt
the string used to generate password ciphertext.
nonce
The string used for encrypted transmission, which is randomly generated and valid for only 1000ms. This means that steps 2-4 must be completed within 1000ms, otherwise the process has to restart from step 1.
JSON
Copy
{ "jsonrpc": "2.0", "method": "challenge", "params": { "username": "root" }, "id": 0 }
Request Example
​
JSON
Copy
{ "jsonrpc": "2.0", "result": { "alg": 1, "salt": "shGzEq91", "nonce": "SGgyhFWf3lFrIpX2BFImBjE1gv2AKPC2" }, "id": 0 }
Response Example
​
Step2: Generate ciphertext using openssl algorithm
The plaintext of your password and salt are used to generate the matching ciphertext. The algorithm is specified by alg.
The ciphertext is a standard unix-like password generated by the algorithm in openssl. It is the same as the value stored in /etc/shadow.
Bash
Copy
cipherPassword=$(openssl passwd -$alg -salt "$salt" "$password")
​
In some other languages, you can replace openssl with other libraries, such as :
JavaScript
Copy
const up = require('unixpass'); const cipherPassword = up.crypt(password, '$' + alg + '$' + salt + '$');
​
Python
Copy
from passlib.hash import md5_crypt, sha256_crypt, sha512_crypt if alg == 1: # MD5 cipher_password = md5_crypt.using(salt=salt).hash(password) elif alg == 5: # SHA-256 cipher_password = sha256_crypt.using(salt=salt, rounds=5000).hash(password) elif alg == 6: # SHA-512 cipher_password = sha512_crypt.using(salt=salt, rounds=5000).hash(password)
​
As example, using the data from the response example in step 1, we can get the ciphertext password is $1$shGzEq91$.TLXit4pO5gGOdru0MYHz.
Step3: Generate hash values for login
The interface does not transmit the ciphertext password directly, but uses it to construct a hash value for verification.
Using a colon : as a concatenator, the username, cipherPassword, and nonce are concatenated to get the string {username}:{cipherPassword}:{nonce}. Then get the hash value by using MD5 algorithm on this string.
As example, using the data from the response example in step 1-2, we can get the string is root:$1$shGzEq91$.TLXit4pO5gGOdru0MYHz.:SGgyhFWf3lFrIpX2BFImBjE1gv2AKPC2, then get the hash value is 6e5fd33bbd77a67eb108cf0b8bbdb9be.
Step4: Get sid by login
Call the login method, passing the username as the username parameter and the hash value as the hash parameter.
This method responds with the sid used for authentication. The validity of the sid is 5 minutes and will be reset each time you call the interface with it. That is, if you don't call any interface for 5 minutes, you need to get the sid again.
JSON
Copy
{ "jsonrpc": "2.0", "method": "login", "params": { "username": "root", "hash": "6e5fd33bbd77a67eb108cf0b8bbdb9be" }, "id": 0 }
Request Example
​
JSON
Copy
{ "jsonrpc": "2.0", "result": { "username": "root", "sid": "AlVv2SolJU3jezHDpreZ5KDm8102f09q" }, "id": 0 }
Response Example
​
Step5: Calling other APIs with sid
Now, you can use sid to call other functional APIs. The other functional APIs call the call method uniformly, passing sid, module-name, function_name and parameters in params array in that order.
Using the get_status API of the system module as an example:
JSON
Copy
{ "jsonrpc": "2.0", "method": "call", "params": [ "AlVv2SolJU3jezHDpreZ5KDm8102f09q", // sid "system", // module-name "get_status" // function_name ], "id": 0 }
Request Example
​
Example
JavaScript
JavaScript
Copy
const axios = require('axios'); const up = require('unixpass'); const crypto = require('crypto'); const url = 'http://192.168.8.1/rpc'; const username = 'root'; const password = 'goodlife'; // Step1: Get encryption parameters by challenge method axios .post(url, { jsonrpc: '2.0', method: 'challenge', params: { username: username }, id: 0 }) .then((response) => { const result = response.data.result; const alg = result.alg; const salt = result.salt; const nonce = result.nonce; // Step2: Generate cipher text using openssl algorithm const cipherPassword = up.crypt(password, '$' + alg + '$' + salt + '$'); // Step3: Generate hash values for login const data = `${username}:${cipherPassword}:${nonce}`; const hash_value = crypto.createHash('md5').update(data).digest('hex'); // Step4: Get sid by login axios .post(url, { jsonrpc: '2.0', method: 'login', params: { username: 'root', hash: hash_value }, id: 0 }) .then((response) => { const sid = response.data.result.sid; // Step5: Calling other APIs with sid axios .post(url, { jsonrpc: '2.0', method: 'call', params: [ sid, 'system', 'get_status' ], id: 0 }) .then((response) => { console.log(JSON.stringify(response.data)); }) .catch((error) => { console.error('Request Exception:', error); }); }) .catch((error) => { console.error('Request Exception:', error); }); }) .catch((error) => { console.error('Request Exception:', error); });
​
Python
Python
Copy
import requests import hashlib from passlib.hash import md5_crypt, sha256_crypt, sha512_crypt url = 'http://192.168.8.1/rpc' username = 'root' password = 'goodlife' try: # Step1: Get encryption parameters by challenge method challenge_data = { 'jsonrpc': '2.0', 'method': 'challenge', 'params': { 'username': username }, 'id': 0 } response = requests.post(url, json=challenge_data) response.raise_for_status() result = response.json()['result'] alg = result['alg'] salt = result['salt'] nonce = result['nonce'] # Step2: Generate cipher text using openssl algorithm if alg == 1: # MD5 cipher_password = md5_crypt.using(salt=salt).hash(password) elif alg == 5: # SHA-256 cipher_password = sha256_crypt.using(salt=salt, rounds=5000).hash(password) elif alg == 6: # SHA-512 cipher_password = sha512_crypt.using(salt=salt, rounds=5000).hash(password) else: raise ValueError('Unsupported algorithm') # Step3: Generate hash values for login data = f"{username}:{cipher_password}:{nonce}" hash = hashlib.md5(data.encode()).hexdigest() # Step4: Get sid by login login_data = { 'jsonrpc': '2.0', 'method': 'login', 'params': { 'username': username, 'hash': hash }, 'id': 0 } response = requests.post(url, json=login_data) response.raise_for_status() result = response.json()['result'] sid = result['sid'] # Step5: Calling other APIs with sid system_status_data = { 'jsonrpc': '2.0', 'method': 'call', 'params': [ sid, 'system', 'get_status' ], 'id': 0 } response = requests.post(url, json=system_status_data) response.raise_for_status() print(response.json()) except requests.exceptions.RequestException as e: print("Request Exception:", e) except (KeyError, ValueError) as e: print("Parameter Exception:", e) except Exception as e: print("An error has occurred:", e)
​
Shell
Bash
Copy
#!/bin/bash host=$1 username=$2 password=$3 # Step1: Get encryption parameters by challenge method challengeResponse="$(curl -k http://$host/rpc -d '{"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"challenge","params":{"username":"'$username'"},"id":0}' 2>/dev/null)" salt="$(echo $challengeResponse|awk -F "salt" '{print $2}'|cut -d '"' -f 3)" nonce="$(echo $challengeResponse|awk -F "nonce" '{print $2}'|cut -d '"' -f 3)" alg="$(echo $challengeResponse|awk -F "alg" '{print $2}'|awk -F ":|," '{print $2}')" echo $challengeResponse # Step2: Generate cipher text using openssl algorithm cipherPassword=$(openssl passwd -$alg -salt "$salt" "$password") echo $cipherPassword # Step3: Generate hash values for login hash=$(echo -n "$username:$cipherPassword:$nonce" | md5sum | cut -d' ' -f1) echo $hash # Step4: Get sid by login loginResponse="$(curl -k http://$host/rpc -d '{"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"login","params":{"username":"'$username'", "hash":"'$hash'"},"id":0}' 2>/dev/null)" sid="$(echo $loginResponse|awk -F "sid" '{print $2}'|cut -d '"' -f 3)" echo $sid # Step5: Calling other APIs with sid statusResponse="$(curl -k http://$host/rpc -d '{"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"call","params":["'$sid'","system","get_status"],"id":0}' 2>/dev/null)" echo $statusResponse
​
Java
Java
Copy
import java.io.BufferedReader; import java.io.IOException; import java.io.InputStreamReader; import java.io.OutputStream; import java.net.HttpURLConnection; import java.net.URL; import org.json.JSONObject; import org.json.JSONArray; import org.apache.commons.codec.digest.Crypt; import org.apache.commons.codec.digest.DigestUtils; public class LoginDemo { private static final String URL = "http://192.168.8.1/rpc"; private static final String USERNAME = "root"; private static final String PASSWORD = "goodlife"; public static void main(String[] args) { try { // Step1: Get encryption parameters by challenge method JSONObject challengeRequest = new JSONObject() .put("jsonrpc", "2.0") .put("method", "challenge") .put("params", new JSONObject().put("username", USERNAME)) .put("id", 0); JSONObject challengeResponse = sendRequest(URL, challengeRequest.toString()); JSONObject challengeResult = challengeResponse.getJSONObject("result"); int alg = challengeResult.getInt("alg"); String salt = challengeResult.getString("salt"); String nonce = challengeResult.getString("nonce"); // Step2: Generate cipher text using openssl algorithm String cipherPassword = Crypt.crypt(PASSWORD, "$" + alg + "$" + salt); // Step3: Generate hash values for login String hash = DigestUtils.md5Hex(USERNAME + ":" + cipherPassword + ":" + nonce); // Step4: Get sid by login JSONObject loginRequest = new JSONObject() .put("jsonrpc", "2.0") .put("method", "login") .put("params", new JSONObject() .put("username", USERNAME) .put("hash", hash)) .put("id", 0); JSONObject loginResponse = sendRequest(URL, loginRequest.toString()); String sid = loginResponse.getJSONObject("result").getString("sid"); // Step5: Calling other APIs with sid JSONObject systemStatusRequest = new JSONObject() .put("jsonrpc", "2.0") .put("method", "call") .put("params", new JSONArray() .put(sid) .put("system") .put("get_status")) .put("id", 0); JSONObject systemStatusResponse = sendRequest(URL, systemStatusRequest.toString()); System.out.println(systemStatusResponse.toString()); } catch (IOException e) { e.printStackTrace(); } } private static JSONObject sendRequest(String url, String request) throws IOException { HttpURLConnection connection = null; try { URL apiUrl = new URL(url); connection = (HttpURLConnection) apiUrl.openConnection(); connection.setRequestMethod("POST"); connection.setRequestProperty("Content-Type", "application/json"); connection.setDoOutput(true); OutputStream outputStream = connection.getOutputStream(); outputStream.write(request.getBytes()); outputStream.flush(); int responseCode = connection.getResponseCode(); if (responseCode == HttpURLConnection.HTTP_OK) { BufferedReader reader = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(connection.getInputStream())); StringBuilder response = new StringBuilder(); String line; while ((line = reader.readLine()) != null) { response.append(line); } return new JSONObject(response.toString()); } else { throw new IOException("Request Exception: " + responseCode); } } finally { if (connection != null) { connection.disconnect(); } } } }
​

Dart

YAML
Copy
dependencies: dio: any crypto: any gl_crypt: git: url: https://github.com/gl-inet/gl_crypt_dart.git
​
Dart
Copy
final String url = 'http://192.168.8.1/rpc'; final String username = 'root'; final String password = 'goodlife'; // Step1: Get encryption parameters by challenge method Dio().post( url, data: { 'jsonrpc': '2.0', 'method': 'challenge', 'params': { 'username': username, } }, ).then( (value) { Map result = jsonDecode(value.data)['result']; int alg = result['alg']; String salt = result['salt']; String nonce = result['nonce']; // Step2: Generate cipher text using Crypt Crypt? pw; switch (alg) { case 1: pw = Crypt.md5(password, salt: salt); break; case 5: pw = Crypt.sha256(password, salt: salt); break; case 6: pw = Crypt.sha512(password, salt: salt); break; default: } // Step3: Generate hash values for login String hash = md5.convert(utf8.encode('$username:$pw:$nonce')).toString(); // Step4: Get sid by login Dio().post( url, data: { 'jsonrpc': '2.0', 'method': 'login', 'params': { 'username': username, 'hash': hash, } }, ).then( (value) { Map result = jsonDecode(value.data)['result']; String sid = result['sid']; // Step5: Calling other APIs with sid Dio().post( url, data: { 'jsonrpc': '2.0', 'method': 'call', 'params': [ sid, 'system', 'get_status', ] }, ).then( (value) { Map result = jsonDecode(value.data)['result']; setState(() { status = result; }); print(result); }, ); }, ); }, );

black_white_list/set_config

set blacklist or whitelist
#.black_white_list/set_config
Parameter Definition

Expand request example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "method": "call",
    "params": [
        "",
        "black_white_list",
        "set_config",
        {
            "mode": "black",
            "mac": [
                "08:10:7B:B3:E8:92",
                "94:83:C4:0C:6D:D6"
            ]
        }
    ],
    "id": 1
}

Expand response example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": 1,
    "result": null
}
Request parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
modestringnull[black:blacklist; white:whitelist]
macarraynullthe mac address list set in the corresponding mode.
Response parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
err_code optionalnumbernullError code,-2 : whitelist information is empty.
err_msg optionalnumbernullError message

cable/set_config

set the WAN port access mode
#.cable/set_config
Parameter Definition
type:bool;default:null;desc:set secondwan

Expand request example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "method": "call",
    "params": [
        "",
        "cable",
        "set_config",
        {
            "protocol": "pppoe",
            "username": "test",
            "password": "123456"
        }
    ],
    "id": 1
}

Expand response example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": 1,
    "result": {}
}
Request parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
protocolstringnullidentifies how protocol the WAN port obtains IP[dhcp; static; pppoe]
usernameoptionalstringnullset the PPPoE username, required when set as PPPoE
passwordoptionalstringnullset the PPPoE password, required when set as PPPoE
vlanidoptionalnumbernullset the PPPoE password, required when set as PPPoE, range 1-4094, 0 by default
ipv6optionalobjectnullset the IPv6 info, required when IPv6 is enabled and set as static IP
ipv6.ipoptionalstringnullIPv6 address
ipv6.gatewayoptionalstringnullIPv6 gateway
ipv6.dnsoptionalarraynullIPv6 DNS
ipv4optionalobjectnullset the IPv4 info, required when set as static IP
ipv4.ipoptionalstringnullIPv4 address
ipv4.netmaskoptionalstringnullIPv4 netmask
ipv4.gatewayoptionalstringnullIPv4 gateway
ipv4.dnsoptionalarraynullIPv4 DNS
secondwanoptionalboolnullset secondwan
Response parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
err_codeoptionalnumbernullerror code [-1: parameter error; -2: ip format error]
err_msgoptionalstringnullerror message

cable/change_interface

set wan port mode
#.cable/change_interface
Parameter Definition
type:bool;default:null;desc:set lan port mode [0: wan; 1: lan]

Expand request example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "method": "call",
    "params": [
        "",
        "cable",
        "change_interface",
        {
            "mode": 1
        }
    ],
    "id": 1
}

Expand response example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": 1,
    "result": {}
}
Request parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
modenumbernullset the WAN port mode [0: work as WAN; 1: work as LAN]
secondwanoptionalboolnullset lan port mode [0: wan; 1: lan]
Response parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
err_codeoptionalnumbernullerror code [-1: parameter error; -6: remove internet cable]
err_msgoptionalstringnullerror message

cable/get_status

get the wan port status
#.cable/get_status
Parameter Definition

Expand request example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "method": "call",
    "params": [
        "",
        "cable",
        "get_status",
        {}
    ],
    "id": 1
}

Expand response example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": 1,
    "result": {
        "mode": 0,
        "status": 1,
        "protocol": "static",
        "ipv4": {
            "ip": "192.168.113.137/24",
            "gateway": "192.168.113.1",
            "dns": [
                "8.8.8.8",
                "8.8.4.4"
            ]
        }
    }
}
Request parameters：
No parameters
Response parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
modenumbernullthe WAN status [0: work as WAN; 1: work as LAN; 2: bridge mode; 3: drop-in gateway mode; 4: passthrough mode]
protocoloptionalstringnullidentifies how protocol the WAN port obtains IP [dhcp; static; pppoe]
statusnumbernullthe connection status [0: connect failed; 1: connect success; 2: connecting; 3: not connect phycially]
ipv6optionalobjectnullIPv6 info, return when the status is 1 and IPv6 is enabled
ipv6.ipoptionalstringnullIPv6 address
ipv6.gatewayoptionalstringnullIPv6 gateway
ipv6.dnsoptionalarraynullIPv6 DNS
ipv4optionalobjectnullIPv4 info, return when the status is 1
ipv4.ipoptionalstringnullIPv4 address
ipv4.gatewayoptionalstringnullIPv4 gateway
ipv4.dnsoptionalarraynullIPv4 DNS
logoptionalstringnullPPPoE info, return when set as PPPoE
passthroughoptionalstringnullpassthrough info, return when set as passthrough
passthrough.enableoptionalstringnullpassthrough status [0: disabled; 1: enabled]
passthrough.ipoptionalstringnullpassthrough mode, IPv4 address
passthrough.gatewayoptionalstringnullpassthrough mode IPv4 gateway
passthrough.netmaskoptionalstringnullpassthrough mode IPv4 netmask
passthrough.dnsoptionalstringnullpassthrough mode IPv4 dns
secondwanobjectnullsecondwan status information
err_codeoptionalnumbernullerror code [-4: this device doesn't have the phycial WAN port; -5: this device doesn't have the virtual WAN port]
err_msgoptionalstringnullerror message

cable/get_config

get the wan port config
#.cable/get_config
Parameter Definition
type:bool;default:null;desc:get secondwan config

Expand request example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "method": "call",
    "params": [
        "",
        "cable",
        "get_config",
        {}
    ],
    "id": 1
}

Expand response example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": 1,
    "result": {
        "protocol": "static",
        "ipv4": {
            "ip": "192.168.113.137",
            "netmask": "255.255.255.0",
            "gateway": "192.168.113.1",
            "dns": [
                "8.8.8.8",
                "8.8.4.4"
            ]
        }
    }
}
Request parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
secondwanoptionalboolnullget secondwan config
Response parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
protocoloptionalstringnullidentifies how protocol the WAN port obtains IP [dhcp; static; pppoe]
ipv6optionalobjectnullIPv6 info, return when IPv6 is enabled and set as static IP
ipv6.ipoptionalstringnullIPv6 address
ipv6.gatewayoptionalstringnullIPv6 gateway
ipv6.dnsoptionalarraynullIPv6 DNS
ipv4optionalobjectnullIPv4 info, return when set as static IP
ipv4.ipoptionalstringnullIPv4 address
ipv4.netmaskoptionalstringnullIPv4 netmask
ipv4.gatewayoptionalstringnullIPv4 gateway
ipv4.dnsoptionalarraynullIPv4 DNS
usernameoptionalstringnullPPPoE username, return when set as PPPoE
passwordoptionalstringnullPPPoE password, return when set as PPPoE
vlanidoptionalnumbernullPPPoE VLAN ID, return when set as PPPoE
err_codeoptionalnumbernullerror code [-4: this device doesn't have the phycial WAN port; -5: this device doesn't have the virtual WAN port]
err_msgoptionalstringnullerror message

clients/get_list

Get device list
#.clients/get_list
Parameter Definition

Expand request example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "method": "call",
    "id": 1,
    "params": [
        "",
        "clients",
        "get_list",
        {}
    ]
}

Expand response example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": 1,
    "result": {
        "clients": [
            {
                "mac": "18:c0:4d:dc:4f:cc",
                "type": 2,
                "limit_tx": 2048,
                "limit_rx": 2048,
                "remote": false,
                "name": "DESKTOP-HO0T5C1",
                "vendor": "unknown",
                "ip": "192.168.8.148",
                "tx": 0,
                "total_rx": 397117728,
                "rx": 0,
                "blocked": false,
                "iface": "eth0",
                "online": true,
                "online_time": "1638517436",
                "total_tx": 470371319
            }
        ]
    }
}
Request parameters：
No parameters
Response parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
clientsarraynullClient list
clients[x].macstringnullClient MAC address
clients[x].ipstringnullClient IP address
clients[x].txnumbernullUplink rate of the client (Unit: Bps)
clients[x].rxnumbernullThe downlink rate of the client (Unit: Bps)
clients[x].total_txnumbernullAll upstream traffic of the client(Unit:Byte)
clients[x].total_rxnumbernullAll downstream traffic of the client(Unit:Byte)
clients[x].limit_txnumbernullSet uplink rate of client speed limit(Unit:KB/S)
clients[x].limit_rxnumbernullSet downlink rate of client speed limit(Unit:KB/S)
clients[x].blockedboolnullGL.iNet firewall blacklist, true means to join the blacklist, false means not to join the blacklist
clients[x].online_timestringnullTimestamp when the client came online
clients[x].onlineboolnullTrue is online, false is offline
clients[x].ifacestringnullThe interface name that the client connects to
clients[x].typenumbernullInterface type of client connection,[{0-2.4G};{1-5G};{2-lan};{3-2.4G guest};{4-5G guest};{5-unknown},{6-Dongle},{7-bypass route}]
clients[x].nameoptionalstringnull The hostname of the client device (no value is returned)
clients[x].remoteboolnullIf true, it means that the current client is connecting to the router
clients[x].aliasoptionalstringnull The name of the user setting (no value is returned)
clients[x].classoptionalstringnull The device type set by the user (No value is not returned)
err_codeoptionalnumbernullError code.
err_msgoptionalstringnullError message.

clients/remove_offline

Delete offline client
#.clients/remove_offline
Parameter Definition

Expand request example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "method": "call",
    "id": 1,
    "params": [
        "",
        "clients",
        "remove_offline",
        {
            "mac": "FF:FF:FF:FF:FF:FF"
        }
    ]
}

Expand response example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": 1,
    "result": null
}
Request parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
macstringnullThe mac address of the client to be deleted (if the value is FF:FF:FF:FF:FF:FF, it means to delete all offline clients)
Response parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
err_codeoptionalnumbernullError code, -1:Invalid user,-5:No parameter found.
err_msgoptionalstringnullError message.

clients/block_client

Set the client's blacklist property
#.clients/block_client
Parameter Definition
type:bool;default:null;desc:If true, the client of the specified mac cannot access the Internet

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "method": "call",
    "id": 1,
    "params": [
        "",
        "clients",
        "block_client",
        {
            "mac": "84:7a:88:79:e5:13",
            "block": true
        }
    ]
}

Expand response example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": 1,
    "result": null
}
Request parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
macstringnullThe mac address of the client to be blacklisted
blockboolnullIf true, the client of the specified mac cannot access the Internet
Response parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
err_codeoptionalnumbernullError code, -1:Invalid user,-5:No parameter found.
err_msgoptionalstringnullError message.

type:bool;default:null;desc:clear token

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": 1,
    "method": "call",
    "params": [
        "",
        "cloud",
        "set_config",
        {
            "cloud_enable": "true",
            "rtty_ssh": "true",
            "rtty_web": "true",
            "serverzone": "China"
        }
    ]
}

Expand response example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": 1,
    "result": {}
}
Request parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
cloud_enableboolnullenable connect to cloud
rtty_sshboolnullenable rtty ssh
rtty_webboolnullenable rtty web
clear_tokenboolnullclear token
serverzonestringnullserver zone
server_namestringnullserver name(serverzone server_name pick one of two)
templetenumbernulltemplate state(valid for 2B)
Response parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
err_codeoptionalnumbernullerror code
err_msgoptionalstringnullerror message

netmaskstringnullSet a new subnet mask.
enablenumbernullset dhcp server enable[1:enable; 0:disable]

dnsarraynullset dns server

    }

FieldTypeDefaultDescription

sumoptionalnumbernullOutput The total number of crash logs currently stored
err_codeoptionalnumbernullError code,-1:Wrong log sequence number entered.

modems[x].at_portstringnullThe AT command port of the cellular modem
modems[x].data_portstringnullThe data port of the cellular modem, It is used when using the 3G protocol
modems[x].sms_supportboolnullWhether the cellular modem support SMS

modems[x].qcfg_unsupportboolnullWhether the cellular modem does not support to set band by AT+QCFG command (true means it doesn't support this command, need to disable AT command set_band)
modems[x].imeistringnullThe IMEI of the cellular modem
modems[x].namestringnullThe name of the cellular modem (Some modem may include the software version)
modems[x].versionstringnullThe version detail of the cellular modem
modems[x].vendorstringnullThe vendor of the cellular modem
modems[x].protocolsarraynullList of connection protocols supported by the cellular modem (Possible values in the list are 3g, ncm, qmi, qcm, directip, callip)
modems[x].simcardoptionalobjectnullThe SIM card information plugged into the cellular modem (The object is not returned if SIM is not detected)
modems[x].simcard.iccidoptionalstringnullThe ICCID of the SIM card (The value may not be available if the SIM card requires a PIN to unlock)
modems[x].simcard.phone_numberoptionalstringnullThe phone nubmer of the SIM card (The value may not be available if the SIM card requires a PIN to unlock or the SIM card does not store the phone number)
modems[x].simcard.mccoptionalstringnullMobile Country Code MCC (Mobile Country Code) of the SIM card, (Co-identify with the MNC the mobile network operator to which the SIM card belongs, the value may not be available if the SIM card requires a PIN)
modems[x].simcard.mncoptionalstringnullMobile Network Code MNC (Mobile Network Code) of the SIM card, (Co-identify with the MCC the mobile network operator to which the SIM card belongs, the value may not be available if the SIM card requires a PIN)

err_msgoptionalstringnullError message

Response parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
modemsarraynullThe status of all cellular modems in the devices
modems[x].busstringnullThe PCIe path (Format: {domain}:{bus}:{slot}.{func}) or the USB path (Format: {bus}-{port[.port[.port]]}) for the cellular modem, depends on how the modem is connected
modems[x].current_simoptionalstringnullThe SIM card currently used by the device, this value is only available for dual card slot devices [1: SIM 1; 2: SIM 2]
modems[x].switch_statusoptionalnumbernullThe state of the device's sim card slots, this value is only available for dual card slot devices [0: Active SIM not switched; 1: Switched to backup SIM due to failover]
modems[x].simcardoptionalobjectnullThe status of the SIM card plugged into the cellular modem(this object will not be returned if no SIM card is recognized)
modems[x].simcard.statusoptionalnumbernullThe registration status of the SIM card [0: Registered; 1: Unregistered; 2: SIM card needs to be unlocked by PIN code]
modems[x].simcard.carrieroptionalstringnullThe network operator's name of the SIM card (The value may not be available if the SIM card requires a PIN to unlock or the SIM card does not store the name)
modems[x].simcard.iccidoptionalstringnullThe ICCID (Integrated Circuit Card Identification Number) of the SIM card (The value may not be available if the SIM card requires a PIN to unlock)
modems[x].simcard.phone_numberoptionalstringnullThe phone nubmer of the SIM card (The value may not be available if the SIM card requires a PIN to unlock or the SIM card does not store the phone number)
modems[x].simcard.mccoptionalstringnullMCC (Mobile Country Code) of the SIM card, (Co-identify with the MNC the mobile network operator to which the SIM card belongs, the value may not be available if the SIM card requires a PIN)
modems[x].simcard.mncoptionalstringnullMNC (Mobile Network Code) of the SIM card, (Co-identify with the MCC the mobile network operator to which the SIM card belongs, the value may not be available if the SIM card requires a PIN)
modems[x].simcard.signaloptionalobjectnullSignal-related status of the SIM card (This object is not returned if the celluluar is not registered with the network)
modems[x].simcard.signal.modeoptionalnumbernullNetwork mode [2: 2G mode; 3: 3G mode; 4: 4G mode; 5: 5G mode; 41: 4G+ mode]
modems[x].simcard.signal.strengthoptionalnumbernullOverall signal strength [1: Poor; 2: Fair; 3: Good; 4: Excellent]
modems[x].simcard.signal.rssioptionalnumbernullReceived Signal Strength Indicator
modems[x].simcard.signal.rsrpoptionalnumbernullReference signal received power (Unit: dBm), it only returned in 4G or 4G+ mode
modems[x].simcard.signal.rsrqoptionalnumbernullReference signal received quality (Unit: dB), it only returned in 4G or 4G+ mode
modems[x].simcard.signal.sinroptionalnumbernullSignal to interference-plus-noise ratio (Unit: dB), it only returned in 4G or 4G+ mode
modems[x].simcard.signal.eciooptionalnumbernullEnergy to interference ratio, it only returned in 3G mode
modems[x].networkoptionalobjectnullNetwork status of the cellular modem (this object will not be returned if the cellular interface is disabled)
modems[x].network.statusoptionalnumbernullNetworking status [0: Connected; 1: Connecting]
modems[x].network.txoptionalnumbernullTotal data size transmitted (Unit: Byte), it is only returned in connected status, i.e. network.status is 0
modems[x].network.rxoptionalnumbernullTotal data size receive (Unit: Byte), it is only returned in connected status, i.e. network.status is 0
modems[x].network.ipv4optionalobjectnullIPv4 network status of the cellular modem, the object is only returned in connected status, i.e. network.status is 0
modems[x].network.ipv4.ipoptionalstringnullThe IPv4 address obtained by the cellular modem
modems[x].network.ipv4.netmaskoptionalstringnullThe IPv4 subnet mask obtained by the cellular modem
modems[x].network.ipv4.gatewayoptionalstringnullThe IPv4 gateway obtained by the cellular modem
modems[x].network.ipv4.dnsoptionalarraynullThe IPv4 DNS server list obtained by the cellular modem
modems[x].network.ipv6optionalobjectnullIPv6 network status of cellular modem, this object is only returned if IPv6 is enabled and in connected status, i.e. network.status is 0
modems[x].network.ipv6.ipoptionalstringnullThe IPv6 address (contain the prefix) obtained by the cellular modem
modems[x].network.ipv6.gatewayoptionalstringnullThe IPv6 gateway obtained by the cellular modem
modems[x].network.ipv6.dnsoptionalarraynullThe IPv6 DNS server list obtained by the cellulayixiugair modem
new_sms_countnumbernullNumber of unread SMS
passthroughoptionalstringnullPassthrough information, this object is returned when the device works in passthrough mode
passthrough.enableoptionalstringnullEnabled status of passthrough [0: Disabled; 1: Enabled]
passthrough.ipoptionalstringnullThe IPv4 address from passthrough mode
passthrough.gatewayoptionalstringnullThe IPv4 gateway from passthrough mode
passthrough.netmaskoptionalstringnullThe IPv4 subnet mask from passthrough mode
passthrough.dnsoptionalstringnullThe IPv4 DNS server list from passthrough mode
err_codeoptionalnumbernullError code [-1: Failed to get information]
err_msgoptionalstringnullError message

modem/set_connect

Set the dial-up settings of the cellular modem and connect
#.modem/set_connect
Parameter Definition
type:bool;default:null;desc:Whether data roaming is enabled [0: Disabled; 1: Enabled]
type:bool;default:null;desc:Whether channel filtering(masking) is enabled [0: Disabled; 1: Enabled]

Expand request example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "method": "call",
    "params": [
        "",
        "modem",
        "set_connect",
        {
            "bus": "1-1",
            "mode": 2,
            "config": {
                "description": "111",
                "protocol": "3g",
                "device": "ttyUSB3",
                "apn": "3gnet",
                "service": "CDCWDMA",
                "auth": "PAP",
                "username": "gl-inet",
                "password": "goodlife1",
                "dial_number": "#9999",
                "ttl": 65,
                "ttl_ipv6": 65,
                "pin_code": "1234",
                "apn_use": "1",
                "roaming": true,
                "band_enable": true,
                "band_filter_mode": 1,
                "band_list": {
                    "LTE": [
                        1,
                        2,
                        3,
                        4
                    ],
                    "NR-SA": [
                        1,
                        2,
                        3,
                        4
                    ],
                    "NR-NSA": [
                        1,
                        2,
                        3,
                        4
                    ]
                }
            }
        }
    ],
    "id": 1
}

Expand response example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": 1,
    "result": {}
}
Request parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
busstringnullThe PCIe path (Format: {domain}:{bus}:{slot}.{func}) or the USB path (Format: {bus}-{port[.port[.port]]}) for the cellular modem, depends on how the modem is connected, which can be gotten from the get_info interface
modenumbernullHandle mode, which defines how to handle the submitted settings [0: Apply but not save; 1: Save but not apply; 2: Save and apply]
configobjectnullApply to the target cellular modem or saved settings
config.protocolstringnullConnection protocol used
config.devicestringnullPort of the device used for connection
config.apnoptionalstringnullAPN (Access Point Name)
config.serviceoptionalstringnullService type, it is required only when using 3G protocol, i.e. protocol is 3g
config.authoptionalstring"NONE"Authentication method [NONE; PAP; CHAP; PAP/CHAP]
config.usernameoptionalstringnullUsername for authentication, it is only valid when auth is not NONE
config.passwordoptionalstringnullPassword for authentication, it is only valid when auth is not NONE
config.dial_numberoptionalstringnullDial number, it is required only when using 3G protocol, i.e. protocol is 3g
config.ttloptionalnumbernullData packet TTL (Time to Live), the data packets sent by the cellular interface will be forced to use the value after setting
config.ttl_ipv6optionalnumbernullData packet IPV6 TTL (Time to Live), the data packets sent by the cellular interface will be forced to use the value after setting
config.pin_codeoptionalstringnullPIN code, it required to unlock the SIM card
config.descriptionoptionalstringnullName of saved settings
config.mtuoptionalstringnullMTU (Maximum Transmission Unit)
config.roamingoptionalboolnullWhether data roaming is enabled [0: Disabled; 1: Enabled]
config.band_enableoptionalboolnullWhether channel filtering(masking) is enabled [0: Disabled; 1: Enabled]
config.band_filter_modeoptionalnumbernullChannel filtering mode [0: allowlist mode, only allow the specified channel; 1: blocklist mode, block the use of the specified channel]
config.band_listoptionalarraynullSpecify the list of channels to be allow or block, divided into 3 number arrays LTE, NA-SA, NR-NSA
Response parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
idoptionalstringnullThe ID (as unique identifier) for the saved settings, only returned when saving the settings (mode is not 0)
err_codeoptionalnumbernullError code [-1: The cellular modem was not found]
err_msgoptionalstringnullError message

    ],

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": 1,
    "result": {}
}
Request parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription

target_versionstringnullTarget version to upgrade to
current_versionstringnullCurrent version of the cellular modem
firmware_uploadstringnullFirmware getting method [modem: Cellular modem download; router: Router upload]
hash_typestringnullHash algorithm used to verify firmware integrity
hash_valuestringnullHash used to verify firmware integrity, only sha256sum supported currently
upgrade_typestringnullFirmware upgrade method [full_ota: Full upgrade; delta_ota: Delta update]
Response parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
err_codeoptionalnumbernullError code [-1: Faar modem; -2: The current version is the same as the target version; -3: The upgrade is in progress; -4: The version number of the cellular modem does not match the current version; -5: Some parameters is wrong]
err_msgoptionalstringnullError messageiled to get the version number of the cellul

modem/set_slot_config

Set dual SIM card settings. The API only supports setting the built-in cellular modem
#.modem/set_slot_config
Parameter Definition
type:bool;default:null;desc:Whether enables dual SIM card failover, that is, the backup card is automatically switched when the network of the main card is unavailable
type:bool;default:null;desc:Whether to enable scheduled switching back to the main card

Expand request example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "method": "call",
    "params": [
        "",
        "modem",
        "set_slot_config",
        {
            "bus": "0001:01:00.0",
            "enable_switch": true,
            "current_sim": "1",
            "main_sim": "1",
            "failover_interval": "120",
            "sim1_profile": "f9FQ3vUzMJmih4Ck",
            "sim2_profile": "o2bCZMB53KHk6HAX",
            "enable_timing": true,
            "hour": "05",
            "min": "00"
        }
    ],
    "id": 1
}

Expand response example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": 1,
    "result": {}
}
Request parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
busstringnullThe PCIe path (Format: {domain}:{bus}:{slot}.{func}) or the USB path (Format: {bus}-{port[.port[.port]]}) for the cellular modem, depends on how the modem is connected, which can be gotten from the get_info interface
enable_switchboolfalseWhether enables dual SIM card failover, that is, the backup card is automatically switched when the network of the main card is unavailable
current_simoptionalstringnullThe currently used SIM card slot, which is required when SIM card failover is disabled [1: SIM 1; 2: SIM 2]
sim1_profileoptionalstringnullThe settings ID used for the SIM 1 slot points to a saved settings
sim2_profileoptionalstringnullThe settings ID used for the SIM 2 slot points to a saved settings
sim1_configoptionalstringnullThe settings network configure for the SIM 1 slot.Refer to 'set_connect'
sim2_configoptionalstringnullThe settings network configure for the SIM 2 slot.Refer to 'set_connect'
main_simoptionalstringnullThe main SIM slot, which is required when SIM failover is enabled
failover_intervaloptionalstring300The failover interval time (Unit: Seconds), which is required when SIM failover is enabled
enable_timingboolfalseWhether to enable scheduled switching back to the main card
houroptionalstring03The hours of scheduled switching time, which is required when scheduled switching back is enabled
minoptionalstring00The minutes of scheduled switching time, which is required when scheduled switching back is enabled
Response parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
err_codeoptionalnumbernullError code.
err_msgoptionalstringnullError message

                "ttl_ipv6": 65,

FieldTypeDefaultDescription

devicestringnullPort of the device used for connection

authoptionalstring"NONE"Authentication method [NONE; PAP; CHAP; PAP/CHAP]
usernameoptionalstringnullUsername for authentication, it is only valid when auth is not NONE
passwordoptionalstringnullPassword for authentication, it is only valid when auth is not NONE
dial_numberoptionalstringnullDial number, it is required only when using 3G protocol, i.e. protocol is 3g
ttloptionalnumbernullData packet TTL (Time to Live), the data packets sent by the cellular interface will be forced to use the value after setting
ttl_ipv6optionalnumbernullData packet IPV6 TTL (Time to Live), the data packets sent by the cellular interface will be forced to use the value after setting
pin_codeoptionalstringnullPIN code, it required to unlock the SIM card
descriptionoptionalstringnullName of saved settings
mtuoptionalstringnullMTU (Maximum Transmission Unit)
roamingoptionalboolnullWhether data roaming is enabled [0: Disabled; 1: Enabled]
band_enableoptionalboolnullWhether channel filtering(masking) is enabled [0: Disabled; 1: Enabled]
band_filter_modeoptionalnumbernullChannel filtering mode [0: allowlist mode, only allow the specified channel; 1: blocklist mode, block the use of the specified channel]
band_listoptionalarraynullSpecify the list of channels to be allow or block, divided into 3 number arrays LTE, NA-SA, NR-NSA
err_codeoptionalnumbernullError code [-1: The cellular modem was not found]
err_msgoptionalstringnullError message

mwan3/set_interface

set mwan3 interface detection type
#.mwan3/set_interface
Parameter Definition
type:bool;default:null;desc:enable detection
type:bool;default:null;desc:enable ssl [for httping way]

Expand request example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "method": "call",
    "params": [
        "",
        "mwan3",
        "set_interface",
        {
            "enable_check": true,
            "interface": "wan",
            "track_proto": 0,
            "track_method": 0,
            "interval": 5,
            "up": 8,
            "down": 3,
            "ipv4": [
                "8.8.4.4",
                "8.8.8.8",
                "208.67.222.222",
                "208.67.220.220"
            ],
            "ipv6": [
                "2001:4860:4860::8844",
                "2001:4860:4860::8888",
                "2620:0:ccd::2",
                "2620:0:ccc::2"
            ]
        }
    ],
    "id": 1
}

Expand response example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": 1,
    "result": null
}
Request parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
enable_checkboolnullenable detection
interfacestringnulldetetction interface name
track_protonumbernulldetection protocol [0: ipv4 only; 1: ipv6 only; 2: both ipv4 & ipv6]
track_methodnumbernulldetection way [0: ping; 1: httping]
enable_sslboolnullenable ssl [for httping way]
intervalnumbernulldetection interval
upnumbernullthe number of successful detections to treat the link as active
downnumbernullthe number of failure detections to treat the link as inactive
track_ipv4arraynulldetection ipv4 address [array of string]
track_ipv6arraynulldetection ipv6 address [array of string]
Response parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
err_codenumbernullerror code
err_msgstringnullerror message

NetworkobjectnullThread network information
Network.ChannelnumbernullThread network channel. The value ranges from 11 to 26
Network.ExtPanIdstringnullThread network Extended PAN ID. Its length is limited to 16 bytes of UTF-8 encoded characters
Network.NetworkKeystringnullThread network key, which is 32 bytes long UTF-8 encoded characters
Network.NetworkNamestringnullThread network name. Its length is limited to 1 to 16 characters
Network.PanIdnumbernullThread network PAN ID, value range: 0<= PAN ID <65535 or 0x0<= PAN ID<0xFFFF
Network.PSKcstringnullThread network PSKc, PSKc is algorithmically generated by Passphrase, ExtendedPanId, and NetworkName,
Network.PassphrasestringnullThread network Passphrase, a user-defined character string that serves as Commissioner Credential and
Network.OnMeshPrefixarraynullOn-Mesh Prefix
Network.LeaderDataobjectnullLeader data
Network.LeaderData.PartitionIdnumbernullPartition ID of the leader node
Network.LeaderData.WeightingnumbernullWeighting of the leader node
Network.LeaderData.DataVersionnumbernullData Version of the leader node
Network.LeaderData.StableDataVersionnumbernullStable Data Version of the leader node
Network.LeaderData.LeaderRouterIdnumbernullLeader Router ID of the leader node
Network.IPv6arraynullIPv6 information
Network.IPv6[x]stringnullIPv6[x] information
Network.ActiveDatasetstringnullOperational Dataset TLVs.
RCPobjectnullRCP information
RCP.StatenumbernullThe state of RCP module, disabled=0, detached=1, child=2, router=3 or leader=4
RCP.RCPVersionstringnullRCP version
RCP.ExtAddressstringnullIEEE 802.15.4 Extended Address
RCP.EUI64stringnullThe factory-assigned IEEE EUI-64
RCP.TXPowernumbernullThe transmit power in dBm
RCP.Rloc16numbernullThread RLOC16 value
err_codeoptionalnumbernullError code.
err_msgoptionalstringnullError message

parental-control/add_group

Add device group.
#.parental-control/add_group
Parameter Definition

Expand request example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": 1,
    "method": "call",
    "params": [
        "",
        "parental-control",
        "add_group",
        {
            "name": "group1",
            "macs": [
                "98:6B:46:F0:9B:A4",
                "98:6B:46:F0:9B:A5"
            ],
            "default_rule": "cfga067b",
            "schedules": [
                {
                    "week": 1,
                    "begin": "12:00",
                    "end": "13:00",
                    "rule": "cfga067c"
                },
                {
                    "date": 2,
                    "begin": "17:00",
                    "end": "18:00",
                    "rule": "cfga067c"
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

Expand response example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": 1,
    "result": {
        "id": "cfga048"
    }
}
Request parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
namestringnullgroup name
default_rulestringnullThe default ruleset ID used by the group. The ruleset ID must correspond to the ruleset ID returned in the rules parameter.
macsarraynullThe device MAC address list contained in the group, which is a string type.
schedulesoptionalarraynullThe list of schedules contained in the group. If there is a schedule setting for the corresponding group, enter this parameter.
schedules[x].weekoptionalnumbernullThe day of the week for the schedule, the allowable range is 0-6, corresponding from Sunday to Saturday.
schedules[x].beginoptionalstringnullThe start time of the schedule, the format is hh:mm, the start time must be before the end time.
schedules[x].endoptionalstringnullThe end time of the schedule, the format is hh:mm, the end time must be after the start time.
schedules[x].ruleoptionalstringnullThe ID of the ruleset to be used by this schedule. The ID of the ruleset must correspond to the ID of the ruleset entered in the rules parameter.
Response parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
idstringnullThe ID of the new group
err_codeoptionalnumbernullError code (-1: missing required parameters, -2: passed shedules but missing required parameters)
err_msgoptionalstringnullError message

parental-control/add_rule

Add a ruleset.
#.parental-control/add_rule
Parameter Definition

Expand request example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": 1,
    "method": "call",
    "params": [
        "",
        "parental-control",
        "add_rule",
        {
            "name": "rule1",
            "color": "#aabbccddee",
            "apps": [
                1001,
                2002
            ],
            "blacklist": [
                "[tcp;;;www.google.com;;]"
            ]
        }
    ]
}

Expand response example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": 1,
    "result": {}
}
Request parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
namestringnullThe name of the ruleset, globally unique, used to distinguish different rulesets.
colorstringnullThe label color of the ruleset, which is used for displaying UI.
appsarraynullThe ID or application type of the application included in the ruleset, which is an integer type, and the corresponding relationship between the application and the ID is returned through the get_app_list.
blacklistoptionalarraynullblacklist The blacklist list of the ruleset, which is a string type. This list follows the application feature description syntax. For the application feature description syntax, please refer to doc.gl-inet.com
Response parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
idnumbernullID of the new ruleset.

appsarraynullThe ID or application type of the application included in the ruleset, which is an integer type, and the corresponding relationship between the application and the ID is returned through the get_app_list.
blacklistoptionalarraynullThe exception list of the ruleset, which is a string type. This list is exceptions relative to the apps parameter. A ruleset can add up to 32 exception features. It follows the application feature description syntax. For the application feature description syntax, please refer to doc.gl-inet.com

FieldTypeDefaultDescription

parental-control/get_config

Get parental control configuration.
#.parental-control/get_config
Parameter Definition

Expand request example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": 1,
    "method": "call",
    "params": [
        "",
        "parental-control",
        "get_config"
    ]
}

Expand response example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": 1,
    "result": {
        "enable": true,
        "drop_anonymous": false,
        "auto_update": false,
        "rules": [
            {
                "id": "cfga067b",
                "name": "rule1",
                "color": "#aabbccddee",
                "apps": [
                    1001,
                    2002
                ],
                "blacklist": [
                    "[tcp;;;www.google.com;;]"
                ]
            },
            {
                "id": "cfga067c",
                "name": "rule2",
                "color": "#aabbccddee",
                "apps": [
                    3003,
                    4004
                ],
                "blacklist": [
                    "[tcp;;;www.google.com;;]"
                ]
            }
        ],
        "groups": [
            {
                "name": "group1",
                "macs": [
                    "98:6B:46:F0:9B:A4",
                    "98:6B:46:F0:9B:A5"
                ],
                "default_rule": "cfga067a",
                "schedules": [
                    {
                        "week": 1,
                        "begin": "12:00",
                        "end": "13:00",
                        "rule": "cfga067c",
                        "id": "cfga066c"
                    },
                    {
                        "date": 2,
                        "begin": "14:00",
                        "end": "15:00",
                        "rule": "cfga067c",
                        "id": "cfga076c"
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}
Request parameters：
No parameters
Response parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
enableboolnullWhether to enable or not.
drop_anonymousboolnullWhether to prohibit anonymous device access.
auto_updateboolnullWhether to automatically update the feature library.
enable_appboolnullWhether to enable the app feature library.
rulesoptionalarraynullList of rulesets, return if ruleset are not empty.
rules[x].idoptionalstringnullRuleset ID, globally unique, used to distinguish different rulesets.
rules[x].presetoptionalboolnullWhether it is a preset ruleset.
rules[x].nameoptionalstringnullThe name of the ruleset.
rules[x].coloroptionalstringnullLabel color of ruleset, used by UI.
rules[x].appsoptionalarraynullA list of application IDs contained in the ruleset, which is an integer type. The correspondence between applications and IDs is returned through the get_app_list.
rules[x].blacklistoptionalarraynullThe exception list of the ruleset, which is a string type. This list is an exception relative to the apps parameter, and follows the application feature description syntax. For the application feature description syntax, please refer to doc.gl-inet.com.
groupsoptionalarraynullDevice group list, if the group list is not empty, it will be returned.
groups[x].idoptionalstringnullGroup ID, globally unique, used to distinguish different device groups.
groups[x].nameoptionalstringnullGroup's name.
groups[x].default_ruleoptionalstringnullThe default ruleset ID used by the group. The ruleset ID must correspond to the ruleset ID returned in the rules parameter.
groups[x].macsoptionalarraynullA list of device MAC addresses contained in the group, which is a string type.
groups[x].schedulesoptionalarraynullThe list of schedules contained in the group. If there is a schedule setting for the corresponding group, this parameter will be returned.
groups[x].schedules[x].idoptionalnumbernullSchedule's ID.
groups[x].schedules[x].weekoptionalnumbernullThe day of the week, the allowable range is 0-6, corresponding to Saturday to Sunday.
groups[x].schedules[x].beginoptionalstringnullThe start time of the schedule, the format is hh:mm, the start time must be before the end time.
groups[x].schedules[x].endoptionalstringnullThe end time of the schedule, the format is hh:mm, the end time must be after the start time.
groups[x].schedules[x].ruleoptionalstringnullThe ID of the ruleset to be used by this schedule. The ID of the ruleset must correspond to the ID of the ruleset returned in the rules parameter.

repeater/set_config

#.repeater/set_config
Parameter Definition

type:bool;default:null;desc:Setup the 20MHz forced mode (with this option enabled, router is forced to work in low bandwidth mode, to get the better stability)
type:bool;default:null;desc:Setup whether the DFS channel is allowed to repeater or not

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",

        "",

        {
            "auto": true,
            "lock_band": "2g"
        }
    ]
}

Expand response example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": 1,
    "result": null
}
Request parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
autoboolnullSetup the enable swith to other saved networks (with this option enabled, router will try to connect to other saved network when the current WiFi doesn't have the Internet access)
antijamboolnullSetup the 20MHz forced mode (with this option enabled, router is forced to work in low bandwidth mode, to get the better stability)
lock_bandoptionalstringnullSetup the repeater band (2g or 5g, null refers to auto)
dfsoptionalboolfalseSetup whether the DFS channel is allowed to repeater or not

#.repeater/scan
Parameter Definition

timer/set_wifi

set wifi config
#.timer/set_wifi
Parameter Definition
type:bool;default:null;desc:set the status of WiFi schedule [true: enable; false: disable]

Expand request example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "method": "call",
    "params": [
        "",
        "timer",
        "set_wifi",
        {
            "wifi": [
                {
                    "band": "5G",
                    "turnoff_min": "11",
                    "enable": false,
                    "func": "turn_onoff",
                    "turnoff_hour": "11",
                    "guest": "0",
                    "week": [
                        0,
                        1
                    ],
                    "turnon_min": "11",
                    "turnon_hour": "11"
                },
                {
                    "band": "5G",
                    "turnoff_min": "11",
                    "enable": false,
                    "func": "turn_onoff",
                    "turnoff_hour": "11",
                    "guest": "1",
                    "week": [
                        0,
                        1
                    ],
                    "turnon_min": "11",
                    "turnon_hour": "11"
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
    "id": 1
}

Expand response example

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": 1,
    "result": {}
}
Request parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
wifiarraynullset the group data of WiFi schedule
wifi[x].enableboolnullset the status of WiFi schedule [true: enable; false: disable]
wifi[x].bandstringnullset the WiFi band [2g; 5g]
wifi[x].guestnumbernullset the WiFi type [0: main WiFi; 1: guest WiFi]
wifi[x].funcstringnullset the WiFi schedule function, turn_onoff refer to turn on and off the WiFi, power_switch refer to switch the WiFi transmission power
wifi[x].turnon_hourstringnullset the start time (hour) of WiFi schedule, required when set as turn_onoff
wifi[x].turnon_minstringnullset the start time (minute) of WiFi schedule, required when set as turn_onoff
wifi[x].turnoff_hourstringnullset the end time (hour) of WiFi schedule, required when set as turn_onoff
wifi[x].turnoff_minstringnullset the end time (minute) of WiFi schedule, required when set as turn_onoff
wifi[x].switch_hourstringnullset the time (hour) to switch the transmission power, required when set as power_switch
wifi[x].switch_minstringnullset the time (minute) to switch the transmission power, required when set as power_switch
wifi[x].restore_hourstringnullset the time (hour) to switch back the transmission power, required when set as power_switch
wifi[x].restore_minstringnullset the time (minute) to switch back the transmission power, required when set as power_switch
wifi[x].switch_powerstringnullset the transmission power switch to, required when set as power_switch [ Max; High; Medium; Low]
wifi[x].restore_powerstringnullset the transmission power switch back to, required when set as power_switch [ Max; High; Medium; Low]
wifi[x].weekarraynullset the days to perform WiFi schedule in a week
Response parameters：
FieldTypeDefaultDescription
err_msgoptionalstringnullerror message
err_codeoptionalnumbernullerror code [-1: parameter error]

wifi_func_5gstringnullget the 5g WiFi schedule function, turn_onoff refer to turn on and off the WiFi, power_switch refer to switch the WiFi transmission power
wifiarraynullget the group data of WiFi schedule
wifi[x].enableboolnullget the status of WiFi schedule [true: enable; false: disable]
wifi[x].bandstringnullget the WiFi band [2g; 5g]
wifi[x].guestnumbernullget the WiFi type [0: main WiFi; 1: guest WiFi]
wifi[x].turnon_hourstringnullget the start time (hour) of WiFi schedule, required when set as turn_onoff
wifi[x].turnon_minstringnullget the start time (minute) of WiFi schedule, required when set as turn_onoff
wifi[x].turnoff_hourstringnullget the end time (hour) of WiFi schedule, required when set as turn_onoff
wifi[x].turnoff_minstringnullget the end time (minute) of WiFi schedule, required when set as turn_onoff
wifi[x].switch_hourstringnullget the time (hour) to switch the transmission power, required when set as power_switch
wifi[x].switch_minstringnullget the time (minute) to switch the transmission power, required when set as power_switch
wifi[x].restore_hourstringnullget the time (hour) to switch back the transmission power, required when set as power_switch
wifi[x].restore_minstringnullget the time (minute) to switch back the transmission power, required when set as power_switch
wifi[x].switch_powerstringnullget the transmission power switch to, required when set as power_switch [ Max; High; Medium; Low]
wifi[x].restore_powerstringnullget the transmission power switch back to, required when set as power_switch [ Max; High; Medium; Low]

}

FieldTypeDefaultDescription

htmodeoptionalstringnullBandwidth(requires device parameter, optional value can be obtained from get interface).
channeloptionalnumbernullChannel (requires device parameter, 0 means automatic, optional value is obtained from the get interface).
txpoweroptionalstringnullTransmission power (requires device parameter, optional values: Max, High, Medium, Low).

enabledoptionalboolnullWhether to enable WiFi (requires iface_name parameter).
ssidoptionalstringnullWiFi name (maximum 32 characters, requires iface_name parameter).
hiddenoptionalboolnullWhether to hide WiFi (requires iface_name parameter).
encryptionoptionalstringnullEncryption method (requires iface_name parameter, optional value can be obtained from the get interface).
